  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "LlamaIndex [19] optimizes the chunking method like Small2Big and sliding window.",
    "Retrieved chunks can be irrelevant and numbers can be large, so reranking is necessary to filter irrelevant documents.",
    "A common reranking approach employs deep language models such as BERT [25], T5 [26], or LLaMA [27], which requires slow inference steps during reranking but grants better performance.",
    "TILDE [28,29] achieves efficiency by precomputing and storing the likelihood of query terms, ranking documents based on their sum.",
    "Retriever and Generator Fine-tuningFine-tuning within the RAG framework is crucial for optimizing both retrievers and generators."
  ],
